All Implemented Interfaces:
org.bukkit.event.Cancellable
public class SuccessfulTradeEvent
extends org.bukkit.event.player.PlayerInteractEvent
This class represents the event which is fired when a player attempts to perform a transaction with a shop. Note: This event is ONLY fired when all the necessary conditions for the transaction are met, and it is fired JUST BEFORE it happens. This makes it possible to cancel the event moments before the trade takes place, by using Cancellable.
